<br>
4 pairs of frogs guard the opening hall, note that the 2nd pair you will see is actually the third pair you will fight, proceed with caution.<br>
<br>
If you can best all 8 frogs you can proceed down the hall, through the door, down a short flight of stairs and face your next challenge.  3 mobs spawn at the end of the hall, one of them can actually be a Scarab, your first possible non-frog mob.  Your actual concern is a Wanderer that will be out of sight to you that is the first possible Krup frog you can encounter also the first mob that may summon you.<br>
<br>
Depending on the location of the Wanderer you will have to kill a total of 11 or 12 mobs (1 of them possibly not a Frog) to move to the spawn point of the 3 mobs where you will be faced with a decision.<br>
<br>
The hall that stretches out to your right leads to Iksar jails and beyond that a Dining Themed area most commonly refered to as Chef.<br>
<br>
Staying close to the left hand wall you can enter a building that will lead you to a zone out pad (just step on it, dont' have to click) heading this way is the safest place to find Golems if you are seeking to fight them for the honor of battle or their possible loot.<br>
<br>
Directly in front of the building there is a bridge leading to a large open area, you should see a Scarab visible on an outcropping along a tunnel that leads deeper into Sebilis beyond the open area.  This area is most commonly called Guardian for the named mob that can drop the awe inspiring Lamentation.<br>
<br>
Even further in, at the end of that tunnel, only accessible by a rogue of some talent, who hasn't forgotten their lockpicks, or by exploiting to bypass the locked door you can enter the Crypt.  Populated almost exclusively by Undead mobs it is home to one of 3 level 60 mobs in the zone who although on an approximately half hour timer has a place holder unlike the 2 other level 60 mobs in the zone who spawn every 2h consistently.<br>
<br>
The Crypt offers by far the most varied loot in the zone and virtually all dropped Kunark spells can be found within the Crypt.  The most redeeming factor of the Crypt to many people is that hunting there requires you to move and fight moreso than any other camp in the zone.<br>
<br>
If instead of travelling across the bridge to the open area you continue across the face of the building to another bridge you are headed to the Disco area, so named for an apparent dance floor with a large red orb for a ceiling.  This camp offers the highest concentration of mobs and also produces more Illis frogs than any of the camps listed to date.  Illis would be the key to getting mid 50 spells.<br>
<br>
If you're going to spend a year in the zone you would have been advised to step over the ledge located right near where that first concentration of 3 frogs is located atleast a few times.  Dropping into water so taking no damage and you can now swim to either end of this body of water and head down a column of water and enter Lower Sebilis.<br>
<br>
The fearsome Krup is now the least of the mobs you will face, soon (assuming you don't die or evac) you will begin to encounter a steady suply of Illis Frogs, this is where you want to be to gather mid 50 Kunark spells, among them Call of the Hero.  The drop isn't that unusual and a full group hunting this area will often get mid 50's spells and hunting here a few days will most likely get you any specific mid 50 spell you are seeking.<br>
<br>
Deeper still you can encounter Myconids (Shrooms), Reet Frogs, the most powerful of the frogs, Juggernauts who appear like the Golems but are far more powerful, Gruplinort a lvl 60 named Enchanter Frog, Sebilite Protector a lvl 60 Golem and generally considered the most difficult mob to pull in the zone assuming the most powerful mob in the zone is alive.<br>
<br>
The most powerful mob will remain a secret to you until you actually kill a single mob in the zone and lose faction to him, kind of spoiling the surprise of Sebilis and ToFS and possibly other zones that don't immediately come to mind by incorporating a meaningless faction hit into killing everymob in the zone.<br>
<br>
But easiest way to get Call of the Hero is to get a rare item that someone who has the spell wants/needs or by amassing a small fortune in platinum by killing many simple mobs for direct cash loot or items that are popular for sale.  And easy is gud. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1196.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1196.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1196.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=1196.topic&start=81&stop=82>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=1196.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=1196.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1196.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.threadControl?topicID=1196.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1196.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1196.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr alig